Key Match Events: Pakistan beat South Africa by 33 runs to stay in the race for the semi-finals.
Shadab Khan scored 52 runs off 22 balls and took two wickets in the eighth over.
South Africa needed to chase a revised target of 142 in 14 overs due to rain interruption.
Nawaz hit the first six of the match.
Markram misjudged a catch leading to a boundary for Nawaz.
Misfield by Shamsi resulted in a boundary.
Iftikhar Ahmed hit two fours in the 10th over.
Shan Masood was dismissed by Nortje.
Pakistan scored 42/3 at the end of the powerplay.
Babar Azam was caught by Rabada off Ngidi's bowling.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play, leading to a revised target for South Africa.
